docs.abstract: An anatomy materializes of a postmodern pyramid scheme.
docs.snippet: An anatomy materializes of a postmodern pyramid scheme.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the Federal Reserve speaks, it speaks in Fedspeak. A pithy turn of phrase or a striking metaphor can all too easily turn into a headline, causing big market moves and a public backlash. So dry technical language and euphemisms are usually the way to go.

headline.main: Crypto Is Crashing. Where Were the Regulators?
headline.print_headline: Regulators Are M.I.A. While Crypto Crashes

docs.abstract: As cryptocurrency prices plunged and funds failed, strict rules on risky assets helped Wall Street companies sidestep the worst. Retail investors weren’t as lucky.
docs.snippet: As cryptocurrency prices plunged and funds failed, strict rules on risky assets helped Wall Street companies sidestep the worst. Retail investors weren’t as lucky.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last November, in the midst of an exuberant cryptocurrency market, analysts at BNP Paribas, a French bank with a Wall Street presence, pulled together a list of 50 stocks they thought were overpriced — including many with strong links to digital assets.

headline.main: How Wall Street Escaped the Crypto Meltdown
